---

## alwaysApply: true

# UI Automation Framework Standards

## Objective

Create a scalable, maintainable, enterprise-grade UI automation framework using Playwright with TypeScript for the application:

```text
https://practicetestautomation.com/practice-test-login/
```

The framework must support manual test case generation, automated execution, reporting, test data management, configuration management, and CI/CD integration.

---

# Framework Technology Stack

## Mandatory Technologies

* Playwright
* TypeScript
* Playwright MCP
* Page Object Model (POM)
* Allure Reporting
* Node.js
* npm
* ESLint
* Prettier

---

# Application Exploration Rules

Before creating automation:

1. Explore all accessible pages, modules, forms, menus, links, and user flows.
2. Identify:

   * Navigation paths
   * Input fields
   * Buttons
   * Links
   * Validations
   * Success messages
   * Error messages
   * Dynamic elements
3. Document every identified module.
4. Identify reusable components.
5. Identify positive, negative, boundary, and validation scenarios.

---

# Manual Test Case Creation Rules

## Test Case Repository

Create a dedicated folder:

```text
/testcases
```

---

## Module-Based Documentation

Create separate markdown files for every module.

Example:

```text
testcases/
├── Login.md
├── Courses.md
```

---

## Test Case Template

Each test case must include:

```markdown
Test Case ID:
Module:
Title:
Priority:
Preconditions:
Test Data:
Steps:
Expected Result:
Post Conditions:
Automation Candidate: Yes/No
```

---

## Coverage Requirements

Create manual test cases for:

### Positive Scenarios

* Successful operations
* Valid user flows
* Navigation verification

### Negative Scenarios

* Invalid credentials
* Missing fields
* Invalid input formats
* Unauthorized access

### Boundary Scenarios

* Minimum character limits
* Maximum character limits
* Special characters
* Empty values

### UI Validation Scenarios

* Labels
* Placeholders
* Tooltips
* Button states
* Error messages
* Success messages

